'''''Cello Again''''' is an album by bassist and cellist [[Sam Jones (musician)|Sam Jones]] which was recorded in 1975 and released on the [[Xanadu Records|Xanadu]] label.<ref>[http://www.jazzlists.com/SJ_Label_Xanadu.htm Xanadu Records discography] accessed April 28, 2014</ref>
==Reception==
{{Album ratings
| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]
| rev1Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name="Allmusic"/> 
}}
Scott Yanow of [[AllMusic]] states, "Bassist Sam Jones, who had not recorded on cello in 14 years at the time of this session, sticks exclusively to that instrument throughout this enjoyable, boppish set".<ref name="Allmusic">Yanow, S., [http://www.allmusic.com/album/cello-again-mw0000900056 Allmusic Review] accessed April 28, 2014</ref>

== Track listing ==
''All compositions by Sam Jones except as indicated''
# "In Walked Ray" - 4:48  
# "[[Old Folks (1938 song)|Old Folks]]" (Dedette Lee Hill, [[Willard Robison]]) - 5:19  
# "Scorpio" - 5:48  
# "[[You'd Be So Easy to Love|Easy to Love]]" ([[Cole Porter]]) - 5:29  
# "Midnight Waltz" ([[Cedar Walton]]) - 5:34  
# "Angel in the Night"  (Billy Higgins) - 7:19  
# "[[Au Privave]]" ([[Charlie Parker]]) - 4:53

